File: docs/content/docs/guides/resources-prompts.mdx, lines 484-495 (the createItem tool's handle function). The issue is the fetchJSON call on lines 485-488:
```
    const item = await fetchJSON<{ id: string; title: string; url: string }>(
      '/api/items',
      { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify(params) },
    );
```
With printWidth 120 and the scaffolded prettierrc settings (singleQuote: true, arrowParens: 'avoid'), prettier reformats this differently — it wants the arguments on fewer lines since the total width is under 120 chars. The fix is to reformat the fetchJSON call to match what prettier --write would produce with the scaffolded config. Run `prettier --print-width 120 --single-quote --trailing-comma all --arrow-parens avoid` on the code to see the expected formatting, then update the mdx code block to match. Note: this is an mdx documentation file with code blocks inside triple backticks — only the code INSIDE the code fence needs to match prettier output, the rest is prose.
